<item>
            <title>[AMQ-2915] Associated advisory topics aren&apos;t cleaned up when a topic/queue is deleted via AdminView</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-2915</link>
                <project id="12311210" key="AMQ">ActiveMQ Classic</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Basically when you create a queue/topic and connect either a producer or consumer to that queue/topic advisory topics are created; if you later delete the queue/topic the advisory topics aren&apos;t cleaned up.  This could become a problem for folks that tend to create and destroy queues/topics often for whatever reason.  Patch fixes this and adds a test for topics and queues.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
